    "summary": "As a multi-faceted dance-professional, I feel hooked to this artform in many ways. Born in the Netherlands but raised in Catalonia, I studied journalism (BA), choreography (BA) and theatre studies (MA) in Barcelona before moving to Amsterdam in 2014. Still active as a performer and as a dramaturgical advisor for choreographers, I currently focus on thinking, writing and talking about dance. I teach dance history at ArtEZ School for the Arts in Arnhem, and Dance Theory at the Expanded Contemporay Dance BA offered by the AHK (Amsterdamse Hogeschool voor de Kunsten). I am currently engaged in a PhD research on the poetics of Dutch choreographer Hans van Manen, and contribute to Springback Magazine and Movement Exposed Critical Space as a freelance critic. As a content curator, I partner with festivals and dance-houses across Europe such as El Mercat de les Flors de Barcelona, Festival TNT Terrassa, Aerowaves' Spring Forward Festival, or Julidans Amsterdam.",
